{"cursor":"9175","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Capacity utilization' is a concept in economics and managerial accounting which\nrefers to the extent to which an enterprise or a nation actually uses its\ninstalled productive capacity. Thus, it refers to the relationship between\nactual output that 'is' produced with the installed equipment and the potential\noutput which 'could' be produced with it, if capacity was fully used.\n","linknr":130,"url":"Capacity_utilization","recorded":1362665111,"links":22,"instances":["economist"],"pdf":["http://homepage.newschool.edu/~AShaikh/measuring%20capacity.pdf","http://homepage.newschool.edu/~AShaikh/measuring%20capacity.pdf","http://www.cds.edu/download_files/334.pdf"],"categories":["Production and organizations","Production economics"],"headings":["Economic significance","Measurement","Engineering and economic measures","Output gap percentage formula","FRB and ISM utilization indexes","Data","References","External links"],"image":["//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["anwar_shaikh","economist"]],"members":["anwar_shaikh"],"related":["Economics","Productive_capacity","Output","Gross_Output","Bond_market","Inflation","Factors_of_production","Capitalism","Economic_statistics","Michael_Perelman","Federal_Reserve_Board","Federal_Reserve_Board","Institute_of_Supply_Management","Turkish_Statistical_Institute","Michael_Perelman","Susan_Strange","James_Crotty","Anwar_Shaikh_(Economist)"]}